---------------------------------------------------
Intention:
I wish to save time in doing tedious work set up 
the hadoop environment to the machines.
The programs are ugly and simple, discard me when 
you think I'm unbearable :->

---------------------------------------------------
Before using this:
pip ssh or other methods to let "import ssh" work

---------------------------------------------------
Files:
ip_list: list of ips
copy_list: source_dir_1
           dest_dir_1
		   source_dir_2
		   dest_dir_2
copy_conf.py: copy ${source_dir_1} to ${dest_dir_1}
              copy ${source_dir_2} to ${dest_dir_2}
command_list: command_1
              command_2
multi_ssh_multi_operations.py: execute ${command_1}
                               execute ${command_2}

---------------------------------------------------
Usage:
open *.py, search for "USERNAME" and "PASSWORD", then
replace with your username and your password
python multi_ssh_multi_operations.py
python copy_conf.py
